Czech Finance Ministry Plans Wider 2013 Budget Gap, CTK Reports

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-09-06T15:39:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/czech-finance-ministry-plans-wider-2013-budget-gap-ctk-reports.html
The Czech  Finance Ministry  plans to
set the central state budget deficit for 2013 at 110 billion
koruna ($6.3 billion),  CTK  newswire reported, citing a ministry
document.  The ministry proposed a shortfall of 105 billion koruna in
the 2012 state budget draft, the newswire said. The targets for
the 2012 and 2013 overall public finance deficits remain
unchanged at 3.5 percent of gross domestic product and 2.9
percent of GDP, respectively, CTK said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
 placa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  